Dia de Todos los Santos in Guatemala
In Guatemala, on All Saints' Day, communities create gigantic kites to fly messages to loved ones who have passed away.
Families migrate across great distances to reunite. In Guatemala, UNICEF helps keep them healthy.
Some moments of reunification in Guatemala.
In Haiti, Carnival is a huge festival right before Lent, a period of fasting and reflection. To celebrate, people dress in costumes for parades called "défilés".
Diwali is the Hindu Festival of Lights, which celebrates the triumph of light over darkness. To celebrate, families come together and light candles placed in beautiful shapes.
UNICEF finds many ways to help families on the move, like these centers in Greece and Montenegro.
Kids and Families may face hardship, but when they have a chance to rest, kids love to play and create.
To celebrate the end of Ramadan, the Islamic month of fasting, Muslim families around the world celebrate Eid al-Adha with feasting, celebration, and charity.
In Ghana, in the weeks before Christmas, communities dress in festive costumes at family gatherings, parades, and parties, and decorate their churches and houses.
For many families in South Sudan, the conflicts of the past decade meant that many people left grandmothers, uncles, aunts, and even parents, thinking they might never see them again.
Even though Nyachol, Akobo, and Nyaneada's families were torn apart by conflict, UNICEF helped them find their way back together.
Many Asian cultures celebrate the Lunar New Year, usually in January or February, by gathering with families and exchanging gifts.
